WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Free Gift Cards and Tech Items with
Southwest Points: www.fairylandshop.me

2
00:01:50.409 --> 00:01:53.078
Ser Ryam was a strong Lord Commander

3
00:01:53.163 --> 00:01:54.706
of the Kings guard.

4
00:01:55.311 --> 00:01:57.271
But he was ill for some time.

5
00:01:57.441 --> 00:01:59.067
He passed in peace. I hope.

6
00:01:59.152 --> 00:02:00.111
Yes. Your Grace.

7
00:02:00.196 --> 00:02:01.448
He was found to have passed

8
00:02:01.533 --> 00:02:03.365
gently in his sleep.

9
00:02:03.449 --> 00:02:06.308
His remains are being prepared
by the Silent Sisters.

10
00:02:06.393 --> 00:02:09.729
The succeeding Lord Commander.
Ser Harrold.

11
00:02:09.814 --> 00:02:14.110
would like to make haste in finding
Ser Ryam's replacement on the Kings guard.

12
00:02:14.195 --> 00:02:16.197
Your Grace. My lords.

13
00:02:16.603 --> 00:02:19.694
The Kings guard must soon be restored
to its full complement of seven.

14
00:02:20.821 --> 00:02:22.239
With the help of the Hand.

15
00:02:22.324 --> 00:02:24.624
I've invited a number of
fine candidates to court.

16
00:02:24.709 --> 00:02:26.586
All have passed fair trials.

17
00:02:30.445 --> 00:02:32.364
Four ships have now been lost.

18
00:02:32.449 --> 00:02:34.030
The last one was flying my banner.

19
00:02:34.690 --> 00:02:36.652
The Step stones have now
grown into a conflagration.

20
00:02:36.736 --> 00:02:39.100
yet you sit here
and dither about court business.

21
00:02:39.185 --> 00:02:41.311
If you've something
to discuss. Lord Corlys...

22
00:02:41.396 --> 00:02:43.092
I want to know what is to be done

23
00:02:43.177 --> 00:02:45.139
about my ships and my men.

24
00:02:45.224 --> 00:02:46.434
The Crown will compensate you

25
00:02:46.519 --> 00:02:48.646
for your ship and crew.
and make an offering

26
00:02:48.731 --> 00:02:51.817
- to the men's families.
- I don't want compensation.

27
00:02:53.562 --> 00:02:55.939
I want to seize the Step stones by force

28
00:02:56.023 --> 00:02:57.420
and burn out this Crabfeeder.

29
00:02:57.505 --> 00:03:00.295
I am not prepared to start
a war with the Free Cities.

30
00:03:00.380 --> 00:03:03.091
These pirates are not the Free Cities.

31
00:03:03.176 --> 00:03:06.262
Who do you think provides them
with their ships and tender?

32
00:03:06.347 --> 00:03:08.182
In all of its history. my lord.

33
00:03:08.267 --> 00:03:10.116
the Seven Kingdoms have never entered

34
00:03:10.201 --> 00:03:11.911
open war with the Free Cities.

35
00:03:12.049 --> 00:03:13.676
Were that to happen.

36
00:03:13.761 --> 00:03:15.913
the losses would be incalculable.

37
00:03:19.972 --> 00:03:22.891
What reason does
the Crabfeeder have to fear us?

38
00:03:25.283 --> 00:03:27.793
The King's own brother has been allowed
to seize Dragons tone

39
00:03:27.878 --> 00:03:30.733
and fortify it with an army
of his gold cloaks.

40
00:03:30.818 --> 00:03:33.272
Daemon has squatted there
for over half a year

41
00:03:33.357 --> 00:03:35.318
without even a protest from The Crown.

42
00:03:35.403 --> 00:03:37.788
I'll caution you. Lord Corlys.

43
00:03:37.995 --> 00:03:41.925
a seat at the King's table
does not make you his equal.

44
00:03:44.635 --> 00:03:46.371
I have acted. Corlys.

45
00:03:47.255 --> 00:03:49.808
I've sent envoys to Pentos and Volantis

46
00:03:50.304 --> 00:03:52.519
to see if we might find common cause.

47
00:03:52.934 --> 00:03:55.269
Ships and men are at the ready.

48
00:03:56.012 --> 00:03:59.349
The Step stones will be settled
in time.

49
00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:02.009
You have dragon riders. father.

50
00:04:08.213 --> 00:04:09.297
Send us.

51
00:04:13.922 --> 00:04:17.030
It isn't that simple. Rhaenyra.

52
00:04:17.115 --> 00:04:18.658
It would be a show of force.

53
00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:21.201
At least the Princess has a plan.

54
00:04:24.843 --> 00:04:27.387
- I only meant that we should at least...
- Perhaps.

55
00:04:27.555 --> 00:04:31.726
there's some better use
for the Princess's talents. Your Grace.

56
00:04:34.003 --> 00:04:36.051
Why don't you take the Princess
to see about the new

57
00:04:36.136 --> 00:04:38.301
Kings guard posting. Lord Commander?

58
00:04:39.611 --> 00:04:41.582
A fine idea. Your Grace.

59
00:04:43.008 --> 00:04:45.442
This knight will protect you as well.

60
00:04:45.527 --> 00:04:47.070
You should choose.

61
00:05:06.766 --> 00:05:08.559
Ser Desmond Car on.

62
00:05:08.800 --> 00:05:11.012
a fine knight. Princess.

63
00:05:11.097 --> 00:05:13.016
Step forward. Ser Desmond.

64
00:05:15.272 --> 00:05:16.857
Son of Ser Royce Car on.

65
00:05:16.942 --> 00:05:19.254
Ser Desmond has proved strong and steady

66
00:05:19.339 --> 00:05:22.098
in both the tourney lists and without.

67
00:05:22.333 --> 00:05:25.121
While traveling through the Kings wood
on his way to King's Landing.

68
00:05:25.206 --> 00:05:27.895
Ser Desmond recently brought
a would-be poacher

69
00:05:27.980 --> 00:05:29.106
to justice.

70
00:05:39.459 --> 00:05:42.489
You might thank him
for his leal service. Princess.

71
00:05:42.824 --> 00:05:46.153
We thank you for your loyal
service to The Crown. ser.

72
00:05:56.997 --> 00:05:58.629
Ser Rymun Mallister.

73
00:06:01.244 --> 00:06:03.528
Son of Lord Lymond Mallister of Seagard.

74
00:06:03.911 --> 00:06:06.121
Winner of the melee at Cider Hall.

75
00:06:06.243 --> 00:06:09.038
He was the last mounted
of three-and-twenty knights.

76
00:06:09.200 --> 00:06:11.411
Ser Rymun was knighted at eight-and-ten.

77
00:06:11.496 --> 00:06:13.700
Do any of these knights
have combat experience?

78
00:06:14.568 --> 00:06:16.395
Beyond capturing poachers.

79
00:06:24.252 --> 00:06:26.171
Ser Criston Cole.

80
00:06:31.803 --> 00:06:34.301
Son of the steward
of the Lord of Blackhaven.

81
00:06:36.778 --> 00:06:38.739
Be welcome. Ser Criston.

82
00:06:40.678 --> 00:06:42.489
You saw combat in the Storm lands.

83
00:06:42.897 --> 00:06:44.668
Dornish marches. Princess.

84
00:06:45.086 --> 00:06:48.214
I fought for a year as a foot solider
against the Dornish incursions.

85
00:06:49.286 --> 00:06:51.246
Ser Arlan Dondarrion
knighted me after we razed

86
00:06:51.331 --> 00:06:53.184
two of the watchtowers along the Boneway.

87
00:06:58.423 --> 00:07:00.091
I choose Ser Criston Cole.

88
00:07:00.375 --> 00:07:03.692
Let's not be too hasty. Princess.

89
00:07:04.590 --> 00:07:07.677
There's no doubt Ser Criston
is a fine warrior.

90
00:07:07.762 --> 00:07:10.223
but houses such as Crakehall and Mallister

91
00:07:10.308 --> 00:07:12.450
are important allies of The Crown.

92
00:07:12.535 --> 00:07:15.520
Seagard. for instance.
is the realm's prime defense

93
00:07:15.605 --> 00:07:17.273
against reavers from the Iron Islands.

94
00:07:17.358 --> 00:07:18.901
Those men are tourney knights.

95
00:07:19.048 --> 00:07:22.145
My father should be defended by a man
who's known real combat.

96
00:07:23.911 --> 00:07:25.037
Should he not?

97
00:07:27.244 --> 00:07:29.079
Of course. Princess.

98
00:07:29.164 --> 00:07:31.708
Well. let us plan Ser Criston's
investiture then.

99
00:07:39.662 --> 00:07:42.581
The Valyrian capital
was built into a volcano.

100
00:07:42.666 --> 00:07:44.167
much like Dragons tone.

101
00:07:44.756 --> 00:07:47.800
And the dragon lords.
the highest of the nobility.

102
00:07:47.885 --> 00:07:50.804
lived here. at the volcanic face.

103
00:07:50.889 --> 00:07:54.059
closest to the source
of their magic and power.

104
00:07:54.429 --> 00:07:56.223
And this was the Anogrion.

105
00:07:57.766 --> 00:07:59.894
Where the bloodmages worked their craft.

106
00:08:02.328 --> 00:08:04.538
It is truly wondrous what you've built.

107
00:08:04.819 --> 00:08:05.819
Oh no.

108
00:08:06.942 --> 00:08:10.200
I only pore over the histories
and provide the plans.

109
00:08:10.285 --> 00:08:12.579
The stonemasons built the structures.

110
00:08:13.129 --> 00:08:15.778
Do you believe that Westeros
can be another Valyria. Your Grace?

111
00:08:15.863 --> 00:08:18.032
That depends.
whether you speak of the Freehold

112
00:08:18.117 --> 00:08:20.036
at its height or at its fall.

113
00:08:21.249 --> 00:08:22.918
Over a thousand dragons.

114
00:08:23.003 --> 00:08:25.923
a navy large enough to span
the seas of the world.

115
00:08:28.970 --> 00:08:31.889
The glory of Old Valyria
will never be seen again.

116
00:08:33.212 --> 00:08:34.755
Seven Hells.

117
00:08:49.652 --> 00:08:51.403
Tell me. how is Rhaenyra?

118
00:08:52.029 --> 00:08:54.138
- What do you mean?
- Well. these days.

119
00:08:54.223 --> 00:08:56.310
she doesn't say more
than a few words to me.

120
00:08:56.395 --> 00:08:58.564
I think she might find it difficult

121
00:08:59.687 --> 00:09:01.606
to discuss personal matters.

122
00:09:03.256 --> 00:09:04.465
It will take time.

123
00:09:06.629 --> 00:09:08.464
It did when I lost mine own mother.

124
00:09:14.448 --> 00:09:16.367
I wish she would approach me.

125
00:09:17.926 --> 00:09:19.177
What if you went to her?

126
00:09:20.037 --> 00:09:21.831
There are times when I would rather face

127
00:09:21.916 --> 00:09:24.940
the Black Dread himself
than mine own daughter of 15.

128
00:09:27.761 --> 00:09:30.680
I think she would open
herself to you if invited.

129
00:09:31.559 --> 00:09:34.698
You do have such an easy way about you.
Your Grace.

130
00:09:38.824 --> 00:09:41.785
You do not mention our talks to Rhaenyra.
do you?

131
00:09:43.878 --> 00:09:45.004
I just.

132
00:09:46.472 --> 00:09:48.557
I fear that she wouldn't understand them.

133
00:09:49.138 --> 00:09:50.681
No. Your Grace.

134
00:10:03.652 --> 00:10:06.245
It's only been half a year
since my mother died.

135
00:10:06.336 --> 00:10:08.368
and already they tried
to marry my father off

136
00:10:08.453 --> 00:10:10.253
and replace me as heir.

137
00:10:10.432 --> 00:10:12.620
I know those men and how they plot

138
00:10:12.705 --> 00:10:15.589
in their secret councils
when I've been sent away.

139
00:10:15.721 --> 00:10:18.862
You cannot worry at the matters
of lords and kings. Rhaenyra.

140
00:10:21.133 --> 00:10:23.167
What if your father were to remarry?

141
00:10:31.276 --> 00:10:32.948
Your father loves you.

142
00:10:39.102 --> 00:10:41.020
He chose you for his heir.

143
00:10:42.043 --> 00:10:44.587
He didn't choose me. He spurns Daemon.

144
00:11:01.245 --> 00:11:02.788
Kneel with me.

145
00:11:19.342 --> 00:11:21.513
I find this is a way to be with my mother.

146
00:11:23.444 --> 00:11:25.362
Here in the quiet of the Sept.

147
00:11:26.690 --> 00:11:28.233
I feel close to her.

148
00:11:33.269 --> 00:11:36.160
- I know it sounds foolish.
- I don't think it's foolish.

149
00:11:37.885 --> 00:11:40.021
- I don't.
- Good.

150
00:11:43.207 --> 00:11:45.126
Because I thought you might try.

151
00:11:48.179 --> 00:11:51.641
If not for me. then. perhaps for them.

152
00:12:16.145 --> 00:12:18.063
What do I say?

153
00:12:18.878 --> 00:12:20.421
Whatever you wish.

154
00:12:21.796 --> 00:12:23.715
It's only for you and the gods to know.

155
00:12:57.003 --> 00:13:00.173
I want him to see me as
more than his little girl.

156
00:13:02.599 --> 00:13:05.417
Mine own father does not know
the language of girls either.

157
00:13:09.691 --> 00:13:11.526
When I wish to talk with him.

158
00:13:12.569 --> 00:13:14.696
I know that I must make the effort.

159
00:13:18.379 --> 00:13:19.495
Thank you.

160
00:13:30.979 --> 00:13:32.856
Your Grace.

161
00:13:32.941 --> 00:13:34.234
I'm glad we could meet.

162
00:13:34.792 --> 00:13:36.377
I know tempers ran hot today.

163
00:13:36.547 --> 00:13:38.632
and I wanted to assure you
how much I value the bond

164
00:13:38.717 --> 00:13:40.261
between our houses.

165
00:13:40.403 --> 00:13:42.947
Rhaenys is my favorite cousin after all.

166
00:13:44.355 --> 00:13:47.316
I wish to apologize for the tenor

167
00:13:47.400 --> 00:13:49.693
at the Small Council today. Your Grace.

168
00:13:49.777 --> 00:13:51.675
It was not my intent to make offense.

169
00:13:52.451 --> 00:13:56.183
Your fleet is one of the realm's
most important assets. Lord Corlys.

170
00:13:56.604 --> 00:13:58.148
But you must understand.

171
00:13:58.233 --> 00:14:00.652
as King. it is my obligation to avoid war

172
00:14:00.737 --> 00:14:02.620
until such time it is unavoidable.

173
00:14:02.716 --> 00:14:04.878
None among us desire open war.

174
00:14:06.412 --> 00:14:08.664
Might I speak plainly. Your Grace?

175
00:14:09.926 --> 00:14:12.933
I always welcome the unfettered thoughts
of my council.

176
00:14:13.294 --> 00:14:17.417
I fear that the eyes of our enemies
are presently fixed on the Red Keep.

177
00:14:18.366 --> 00:14:19.683
The Queen has passed.

178
00:14:19.881 --> 00:14:21.967
A girl has been named
heir to the Iron Throne.

179
00:14:22.052 --> 00:14:23.737
the first in its history.

180
00:14:23.822 --> 00:14:25.506
The King's brother. so disinherited.

181
00:14:25.591 --> 00:14:27.503
has claimed the Targaryen seat
on Dragons tone

182
00:14:27.588 --> 00:14:29.131
without challenge.

183
00:14:29.800 --> 00:14:32.386
And now. a foreign power
has established a colony

184
00:14:32.471 --> 00:14:34.598
in our most critical shipping lane.

185
00:14:35.761 --> 00:14:39.264
You paint such an aspirant portrait
of my reign. Lord Corlys.

186
00:14:39.349 --> 00:14:41.128
It is an honest one. cousin.

187
00:14:42.285 --> 00:14:45.330
At the moment. The Crown is perceived
as being vulnerable.

188
00:14:45.820 --> 00:14:47.739
And a blind incursion in the Step stones

189
00:14:47.824 --> 00:14:50.076
is the only way to demonstrate
that we are not?

190
00:14:50.161 --> 00:14:53.565
To elude a storm.
you can either sail into it.

191
00:14:53.650 --> 00:14:55.235
or around it.

192
00:14:55.320 --> 00:14:57.780
But you must never await its coming.

193
00:14:59.086 --> 00:15:01.839
Do you have a specific
course of action to propose.

194
00:15:02.312 --> 00:15:03.744
my lord?

195
00:15:05.690 --> 00:15:07.525
Join our families.

196
00:15:08.207 --> 00:15:09.833
Wed our daughter. Laena.

197
00:15:09.917 --> 00:15:12.956
Unite the two great surviving
Valyrian houses.

198
00:15:13.041 --> 00:15:16.073
With the Targaryen dragons
and the Velaryon fleet bound in blood.

199
00:15:16.158 --> 00:15:17.618
you can show the realm

200
00:15:17.703 --> 00:15:20.026
that The Crown's strongest days are ahead.

201
00:15:20.300 --> 00:15:21.385
not behind.

202
00:15:26.097 --> 00:15:27.640
I must admit.

203
00:15:28.278 --> 00:15:30.197
I haven't given marriage much thought.

204
00:15:30.865 --> 00:15:33.159
It hasn't even been half a year
since Aemma passed.

205
00:15:33.244 --> 00:15:36.581
The realm expects you to take a new wife
soon or late. Your Grace.

206
00:15:36.666 --> 00:15:39.565
to strengthen your line
and produce more heirs.

207
00:15:39.665 --> 00:15:42.793
You could not ask for
a stronger match than Laena.

208
00:16:09.577 --> 00:16:11.704
We haven't spoken much

209
00:16:14.388 --> 00:16:15.597
since.

210
00:16:18.866 --> 00:16:20.492
A regret of mine.

211
00:16:22.061 --> 00:16:25.011
We should be free to speak our minds
to one another.

212
00:16:25.599 --> 00:16:27.142
You can say whatever you'd like.

213
00:16:27.227 --> 00:16:28.737
You are the King.

214
00:16:36.715 --> 00:16:40.222
I loved your mother very much.

215
00:16:43.728 --> 00:16:45.021
As did I.

216
00:17:00.621 --> 00:17:03.791
Ser Harrold provided
a fine field of tourney knights.

217
00:17:03.875 --> 00:17:05.001
Oh?

218
00:17:06.085 --> 00:17:07.711
But in questioning them.

219
00:17:07.796 --> 00:17:10.378
I discovered that Ser Criston
was the only man among them

220
00:17:10.463 --> 00:17:12.590
with true battle experience.

221
00:17:13.085 --> 00:17:15.629
He'll make a fine
knight of the Kings guard.

222
00:17:20.868 --> 00:17:24.245
- Today at Small Council...
- Pay it no mind.

223
00:17:24.330 --> 00:17:27.124
- I thought I might have had some insight.
- You're young.

224
00:17:28.061 --> 00:17:29.187
You will learn.

225
00:17:52.925 --> 00:17:56.470
This is our best chance
to save the digit. Your Grace.

226
00:17:58.457 --> 00:18:00.730
The maggots will remove the dead flesh

227
00:18:00.815 --> 00:18:03.360
and hopefully stop the advance of the rot.

228
00:18:08.676 --> 00:18:11.097
I held an audience earlier today

229
00:18:11.182 --> 00:18:13.351
with Lord Corlys and Princess Rhaenys.

230
00:18:13.436 --> 00:18:15.878
That was most charitable
of you. Your Grace.

231
00:18:15.963 --> 00:18:18.841
I'm sure Lord Corlys
appreciated the spirit of it.

232
00:18:18.926 --> 00:18:20.844
He proposed a marriage.

233
00:18:22.033 --> 00:18:24.433
To whom. Your Grace?

234
00:18:25.060 --> 00:18:26.604
The Lady Laena.

235
00:18:27.218 --> 00:18:29.303
To combine the strength of our houses.

236
00:18:29.388 --> 00:18:32.417
and demonstrate my reign's
strongest days are ahead.

237
00:18:32.502 --> 00:18:33.587
not behind.

238
00:18:33.672 --> 00:18:36.049
Lord Corlys has overreached. Your Grace.

239
00:18:36.721 --> 00:18:40.104
Such matters must be discussed
with the Small Council.

240
00:18:40.189 --> 00:18:42.900
That is what I'm doing. presently.

241
00:18:44.161 --> 00:18:47.706
So. what is your advice. dear Otto.

242
00:18:48.746 --> 00:18:50.440
The Lady Laena

243
00:18:51.233 --> 00:18:53.394
is young. Your Grace.

244
00:18:53.722 --> 00:18:56.934
Indeed. but the wounds
made by the Great Council

245
00:18:57.019 --> 00:18:58.558
still linger. my King.

246
00:18:58.762 --> 00:19:01.878
A match with their daughter
would go a long way towards

247
00:19:01.963 --> 00:19:03.965
sealing the breach

248
00:19:04.050 --> 00:19:06.928
and uniting the two great Valyrian houses

249
00:19:07.013 --> 00:19:10.097
would certainly signal unity
throughout the realm

250
00:19:10.331 --> 00:19:11.832
and beyond.

251
00:19:12.130 --> 00:19:14.507
The Grand Maester's reasoning is sound.

252
00:19:16.376 --> 00:19:18.170
I do fear what Rhaenyra might think.

253
00:19:18.255 --> 00:19:20.174
What does it matter. Your Grace?

254
00:19:20.259 --> 00:19:22.425
Her mother has passed.

255
00:19:22.510 --> 00:19:24.888
Her father must propagate the royal line.

256
00:19:31.517 --> 00:19:35.438
I dearly loved my own lady wife.

257
00:19:36.329 --> 00:19:39.248
The pain of her passing still haunts me.

258
00:19:40.918 --> 00:19:42.836
And to be compelled to

259
00:19:43.924 --> 00:19:46.468
replace her for duty's sake.

260
00:19:48.001 --> 00:19:49.544
You are the King.

261
00:19:50.608 --> 00:19:52.526
But I do not envy you.

262
00:20:20.071 --> 00:20:22.616
What was it like flying the Black Dread?

263
00:20:22.893 --> 00:20:25.771
You were Balerion's last rider.

264
00:20:25.997 --> 00:20:29.113
Only for a short time before he died.

265
00:20:29.233 --> 00:20:30.276
With Balerion

266
00:20:30.361 --> 00:20:32.947
died the last memory of Valyria of Old.

267
00:20:33.658 --> 00:20:35.410
But Vhagar still lives

268
00:20:35.902 --> 00:20:37.487
somewhere.

269
00:20:37.572 --> 00:20:39.490
Bit too large for the Dragon pit.

270
00:20:39.856 --> 00:20:42.400
Some would say too large for our world.

271
00:20:43.329 --> 00:20:46.416
- Do you know where she nests?
- I'm sorry?

272
00:20:46.501 --> 00:20:48.434
Do you know where Vhagar is now?

273
00:20:48.519 --> 00:20:51.230
The Dragon keepers believe she made home

274
00:20:51.315 --> 00:20:53.355
somewhere on the coast of the Narrow Sea.

275
00:20:53.440 --> 00:20:56.285
The workers at Spicetown report
hearing her song at times.

276
00:20:56.922 --> 00:20:59.049
They say it is a sad thing.

277
00:21:00.793 --> 00:21:02.965
I imagine even dragons get lonely.

278
00:21:07.218 --> 00:21:08.469
Your Grace.

279
00:21:09.455 --> 00:21:11.415
it would be a great honor

280
00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:15.371
to join our houses
as they were in Old Valyria.

281
00:21:15.558 --> 00:21:17.160
I would give you many children

282
00:21:17.245 --> 00:21:18.895
of pure Valyrian blood

283
00:21:18.980 --> 00:21:21.004
so that we might strengthen the royal line

284
00:21:21.089 --> 00:21:22.457
and the realm.

285
00:21:22.542 --> 00:21:24.711
Is that what your father told you to say?

286
00:21:29.470 --> 00:21:30.930
What did your mother tell you?

287
00:21:32.774 --> 00:21:35.902
That I wouldn't have to bed you
until I turned 14.

288
00:22:02.213 --> 00:22:04.150
It bothers you. does it not?

289
00:22:08.999 --> 00:22:10.642
My father is a king.

290
00:22:11.298 --> 00:22:14.267
It is his duty to take a new wife
and strengthen his line.

291
00:22:14.352 --> 00:22:15.563
I did not ask for a lesson in politics.

292
00:22:15.647 --> 00:22:17.023
I asked whether this bothers you.

293
00:22:17.108 --> 00:22:18.253
Laena is your daughter. Princess.

294
00:22:18.337 --> 00:22:20.005
Does it bother you?

295
00:22:21.267 --> 00:22:22.393
Of course. it does.

296
00:22:24.296 --> 00:22:26.619
But I understand the order of things.

297
00:22:29.017 --> 00:22:30.674
I'm not sure you do.

298
00:22:33.697 --> 00:22:36.783
If you mean to elicit some anger from me.

299
00:22:36.989 --> 00:22:39.742
you should know that
you're failing. Princess.

300
00:22:40.550 --> 00:22:42.093
Quite the opposite.

301
00:22:45.251 --> 00:22:47.050
Whether it's to my daughter
or to someone else's.

302
00:22:47.134 --> 00:22:50.053
your father will remarry sooner than late.

303
00:22:50.792 --> 00:22:53.135
His new wife will produce new heirs.

304
00:22:53.220 --> 00:22:55.822
and chances are better than not
that one of those will be male.

305
00:22:55.955 --> 00:22:58.658
And when that boy comes of age
and your father has passed.

306
00:22:58.743 --> 00:23:01.291
the men of the realm
will expect him to be heir.

307
00:23:01.376 --> 00:23:02.710
not you.

308
00:23:05.177 --> 00:23:07.096
Because that is the order of things.

309
00:23:09.281 --> 00:23:11.575
When I'm Queen. I will create a new order.

310
00:23:13.051 --> 00:23:15.178
How I wish that could be. Rhaenyra.

311
00:23:15.913 --> 00:23:18.415
But the men of the realm
already had their opportunity

312
00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:20.627
to appoint a ruling queen
at the Great Council

313
00:23:20.712 --> 00:23:22.213
and they denied it.

314
00:23:22.331 --> 00:23:25.208
They denied you. Princess Rhaenys.

315
00:23:26.162 --> 00:23:28.123
"The Queen Who Never Was."

316
00:23:28.301 --> 00:23:31.096
But they bent the knee to me
and called me heir to the throne.

317
00:23:31.212 --> 00:23:34.174
Do you remind your father's men of that
as you carry their cups?

318
00:23:38.526 --> 00:23:40.486
Here is the hard truth.

319
00:23:40.570 --> 00:23:43.166
which no one else has
the heart to tell you.

320
00:23:44.161 --> 00:23:47.267
Men would sooner put
the realm to the torch

321
00:23:47.743 --> 00:23:50.572
than see a woman ascend the Iron Throne.

322
00:23:55.182 --> 00:23:57.752
And your father is no fool.

323
00:24:10.905 --> 00:24:13.861
The Small Council is urging me to remarry.

324
00:24:16.258 --> 00:24:18.580
It seems the realm wants for a new queen.

325
00:24:23.788 --> 00:24:26.658
A good and kind queen
will give comfort to your subjects.

326
00:24:31.934 --> 00:24:35.041
Does the Small Council
have a particular lady in mind?

327
00:24:37.149 --> 00:24:40.994
Lord Corlys Velaryon has offered
the hand of his daughter.

328
00:24:41.826 --> 00:24:43.369
the Lady Laena.

329
00:24:44.417 --> 00:24:46.336
A very strong match. Your Grace.

330
00:24:47.581 --> 00:24:51.385
I must admit.
I don't know Laena very well.

331
00:24:51.893 --> 00:24:54.229
I'm sure that she is good and kind.

332
00:24:54.314 --> 00:24:57.859
and that she will enjoy your company.
as I have. Your Grace.

333
00:25:12.735 --> 00:25:14.278
I brought you something.

334
00:25:33.870 --> 00:25:35.913
I asked the stonemasons to mend it.

335
00:25:39.572 --> 00:25:41.533
This is

336
00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:44.794
a very kind gesture. Alicent.

337
00:25:48.804 --> 00:25:50.723
Very kind.

338
00:25:57.261 --> 00:25:59.096
Come.

339
00:26:01.456 --> 00:26:03.583
The Hand. Your Grace.

340
00:26:07.770 --> 00:26:11.148
Your Grace. I've called the Small Council
to an emergency session.

341
00:26:11.232 --> 00:26:12.262
Why?

342
00:26:13.240 --> 00:26:15.575
I think it best you hear it directly.

343
00:26:16.672 --> 00:26:17.996
Very well.

344
00:26:47.793 --> 00:26:51.035
- Daemon.
- The Prince left a missive.

345
00:26:51.120 --> 00:26:52.560
which I believe might explain.

346
00:26:53.496 --> 00:26:56.285
"It is the pleasure of Daemon Targaryen.

347
00:26:56.370 --> 00:26:58.160
"the Prince of Dragons tone

348
00:26:58.245 --> 00:27:01.809
"and rightful heir to the Iron Throne.

349
00:27:01.894 --> 00:27:04.668
"to announce that he is
to take a second wife

350
00:27:04.753 --> 00:27:07.456
"in the tradition of Old Valyria.

351
00:27:07.541 --> 00:27:12.066
"She is to assume the title
Lady Mysaria of Dragons tone.

352
00:27:12.293 --> 00:27:14.254
"Her Grace is with child

353
00:27:14.339 --> 00:27:19.371
"and is to have a dragon's egg
placed in the babe's cradle

354
00:27:19.456 --> 00:27:22.354
in the custom of House Targaryen."

355
00:27:22.643 --> 00:27:26.800
The Prince has invited you
to his wedding. Your Grace.

356
00:27:26.996 --> 00:27:30.249
- It is in two days' time.
- Gods be good.

357
00:27:30.334 --> 00:27:32.336
Who is Lady Mysaria?

358
00:27:32.421 --> 00:27:34.308
- We believe...
- Daemon's whore.

359
00:27:36.320 --> 00:27:39.489
- This is nothing less than sedition.
- I strongly agree. sire.

360
00:27:39.574 --> 00:27:41.701
My brother wishes to provoke me.

361
00:27:42.189 --> 00:27:44.149
To answer is to give him what he wants.

362
00:27:44.234 --> 00:27:46.527
The realm is watching. Your Grace.

363
00:27:46.612 --> 00:27:48.034
What would you have me do?

364
00:27:48.119 --> 00:27:50.037
Send him to the Wall?

365
00:27:50.484 --> 00:27:52.485
Perhaps I could put his head on a spike.

366
00:27:52.570 --> 00:27:54.597
Daemon has seized Dragons tone.

367
00:27:54.682 --> 00:27:57.300
has surrounded himself
with an army of gold cloaks.

368
00:27:57.385 --> 00:27:59.417
and has now stolen a dangerous weapon.

369
00:27:59.509 --> 00:28:01.509
Which egg...
<i>Speaking High Valyrian...</i>

370
00:28:03.711 --> 00:28:05.729
Which egg did Daemon take?

371
00:28:12.686 --> 00:28:16.635
The egg was Dreamfyre's princess.

372
00:28:18.305 --> 00:28:22.940
The samo one you chose
for prince Baelon's cradle.

373
00:28:25.933 --> 00:28:27.935
Assemble a detachment. Otto.

374
00:28:28.874 --> 00:28:31.331
I will go to Dragons tone
and drag Daemon back

375
00:28:31.416 --> 00:28:33.710
- to face justice myself.
- Your Grace.

376
00:28:34.276 --> 00:28:36.698
My apologies. Your Grace.
but I cannot allow it.

377
00:28:36.783 --> 00:28:37.956
It's too dangerous.

378
00:28:38.042 --> 00:28:40.136
Daemon is without limit.

379
00:28:40.784 --> 00:28:42.870
Let me go to Dragons tone.

380
00:29:08.783 --> 00:29:11.565
You're the most comely girl at court.

381
00:29:11.917 --> 00:29:14.044
Why do you destroy yourself?

382
00:29:20.107 --> 00:29:22.234
Will you see the King tonight?

383
00:29:25.016 --> 00:29:26.350
If you wish it.

384
00:29:29.659 --> 00:29:32.268
- Good day. Ser Criston.
- My Lady.

385
00:29:32.469 --> 00:29:35.456
I've assembled 20 of your best
household guards. my Lord Hand.

386
00:29:35.651 --> 00:29:37.668
Sir Harrold will also join us.

387
00:29:41.713 --> 00:29:44.633
Please look after the Hand. Ser Criston.

388
00:31:01.339 --> 00:31:03.722
Welcome to Dragons tone. Otto.

389
00:31:05.706 --> 00:31:08.709
Your occupation of this island
is at an end.

390
00:31:09.634 --> 00:31:11.636
You're to relinquish the dragon's egg.

391
00:31:11.721 --> 00:31:13.180
disband your army.

392
00:31:13.265 --> 00:31:15.058
banish your whore.

393
00:31:16.012 --> 00:31:18.714
and leave Dragons tone
by order of His Grace.

394
00:31:18.807 --> 00:31:21.225
- King Viserys.
- Where is the King? I don't see him.

395
00:31:21.310 --> 00:31:25.106
His Grace would never lower himself
to entertain such a mummer's farce.

396
00:31:29.815 --> 00:31:31.483
Ser Crispin. wasn't it?

397
00:31:31.568 --> 00:31:33.110
Ser Criston Cole. my Prince.

398
00:31:33.195 --> 00:31:35.281
Yes. apologies. I couldn't recall.

399
00:31:35.490 --> 00:31:38.440
Perhaps my Prince recalls
when I knocked him off his horse.

400
00:31:40.240 --> 00:31:41.198
Very good.

401
00:31:41.283 --> 00:31:43.925
This is a truly pathetic show. Daemon.

402
00:31:44.074 --> 00:31:46.003
Are you so desperate
for the King's attention

403
00:31:46.088 --> 00:31:48.964
that you've resorted to skulking about
like a common cut purse?

404
00:31:49.049 --> 00:31:51.198
I'm simply keeping with
the traditions of my house.

405
00:31:51.283 --> 00:31:52.754
the same as my brother did for his heir.

406
00:31:52.838 --> 00:31:55.823
Those traditions are for the true born
children of royalty.

407
00:31:55.908 --> 00:31:58.619
not for bastards fathered
on a common whore.

408
00:31:59.019 --> 00:32:00.979
Lady Mysaria is to be my wife.

409
00:32:01.064 --> 00:32:02.331
This is an abomination.

410
00:32:02.416 --> 00:32:04.315
With every breath you soil your name.

411
00:32:04.400 --> 00:32:06.193
your house. and your brother's reign.

412
00:32:06.278 --> 00:32:08.714
Our love does not know
titles and traditions.

413
00:32:10.182 --> 00:32:12.476
And what of you. men of the City Watch?

414
00:32:12.561 --> 00:32:14.386
Aiding the Prince in his treason?

415
00:32:14.486 --> 00:32:16.183
The King made me their commander.

416
00:32:16.268 --> 00:32:17.603
They are loyal to me.

417
00:32:18.271 --> 00:32:20.190
You've come for the egg.

418
00:32:21.575 --> 00:32:22.826
Here it is.

419
00:32:24.124 --> 00:32:26.001
Are you mad?

420
00:32:26.086 --> 00:32:28.838
- You'd never survive this.
- Well. happily. neither would you.

421
00:32:29.792 --> 00:32:34.671
To chose violence. here.
is to declare war against your King.

422
00:32:34.756 --> 00:32:35.882
Wonderful.

423
00:32:37.124 --> 00:32:40.881
Even if it ends in the death
of your unborn child and its mother?

424
00:33:17.694 --> 00:33:18.820
All of you.

425
00:33:19.431 --> 00:33:21.350
sheathe the fucking steel.

426
00:34:25.581 --> 00:34:28.625
- What are you doing here. Princess?
- Preventing bloodshed.

427
00:34:28.710 --> 00:34:31.496
Ser Criston. please escort
the Princess to safety.

428
00:34:31.757 --> 00:34:33.902
Take care not to startle Syrax. my lords.

429
00:34:34.159 --> 00:34:36.277
She's rather protective of me.

430
00:34:38.009 --> 00:34:42.432
My father named me princess of Dragostone.

431
00:34:42.710 --> 00:34:46.749
This is my castle you're living in. uncle.

432
00:34:46.834 --> 00:34:48.979
Not until you come of age.

433
00:34:49.063 --> 00:34:51.260
You have angered your king.

434
00:34:51.344 --> 00:34:53.344
I don't see why?

435
00:34:53.428 --> 00:34:55.760
This is a day of celebration.
I am to be wed.

436
00:34:55.845 --> 00:34:57.229
You already  have a wife.

437
00:34:57.320 --> 00:34:59.213
No one of my choosing.

438
00:35:00.031 --> 00:35:04.627
And this required you
to steel my brother a egg?

439
00:35:04.711 --> 00:35:09.307
You shared your cradle with a dragon.
when you were born.

440
00:35:10.416 --> 00:35:12.190
You're to have a child.

441
00:35:14.328 --> 00:35:15.854
One day.

442
00:35:24.256 --> 00:35:26.363
I'm right here. Uncle.

443
00:35:28.246 --> 00:35:30.165
the object of your ire.

444
00:35:30.893 --> 00:35:33.621
the reason that you were disinherited.

445
00:35:33.877 --> 00:35:35.900
If you wish to be restored as heir.

446
00:35:36.011 --> 00:35:37.555
you'll need to kill me.

447
00:35:38.747 --> 00:35:39.918
So. do it.

448
00:35:41.010 --> 00:35:43.137
And be done with all this bother.

449
00:37:31.357 --> 00:37:34.193
You announced that we were to be wed?

450
00:37:35.202 --> 00:37:36.745
On the morrow.

451
00:37:38.117 --> 00:37:40.036
And that I was with child.

452
00:37:40.968 --> 00:37:42.552
Your child.

453
00:37:42.637 --> 00:37:45.890
Well. perhaps when we are wed.
we can make that true.

454
00:37:45.975 --> 00:37:49.747
I ensured long ago that I would never be
threatened by childbirth.

455
00:37:49.832 --> 00:37:52.606
Good. Children can be such
irritating creatures.

456
00:37:52.691 --> 00:37:55.277
You swore to protect me. Daemon.

457
00:37:57.071 --> 00:37:59.198
Dragons tone is quite secure.

458
00:38:01.103 --> 00:38:04.747
Until the King decides to reclaim
his ancestral seat.

459
00:38:05.605 --> 00:38:08.357
His men might not put
the Prince's head on a spike.

460
00:38:08.442 --> 00:38:10.694
but what would they do
with the common whore

461
00:38:10.779 --> 00:38:13.177
he claims he's taken to wife
and made with child?

462
00:38:13.262 --> 00:38:14.805
No one will harm you.

463
00:38:15.533 --> 00:38:19.778
I have been sold as property
more times than I care to count.

464
00:38:19.866 --> 00:38:23.286
beginning in a homeland
I can no longer recall.

465
00:38:24.468 --> 00:38:27.805
Most of my years have been spent
living in terror.

466
00:38:28.282 --> 00:38:30.284
You're safe with me. I swear it.

467
00:38:30.369 --> 00:38:31.856
You are Targaryen.

468
00:38:32.023 --> 00:38:35.145
You can afford to play
your stupid games with the King.

469
00:38:35.230 --> 00:38:37.148
but I cannot.

470
00:38:37.952 --> 00:38:41.919
I didn't come into your service
wanting gold or power

471
00:38:42.160 --> 00:38:43.997
or station.

472
00:38:44.537 --> 00:38:48.291
- I came to you to be liberated.
- Liberated.

473
00:38:51.255 --> 00:38:52.423
From what?

474
00:38:53.733 --> 00:38:54.859
Fear.

475
00:39:20.668 --> 00:39:22.336
No. please. Lord Lyonel.

476
00:39:28.323 --> 00:39:30.901
I have come looking for
an unencumbered opinion.

477
00:39:31.013 --> 00:39:33.474
That's all I would ever give. Your Grace.

478
00:39:34.168 --> 00:39:37.565
Ever since my name was read
by the archmaesters at the Great Council.

479
00:39:37.664 --> 00:39:41.042
I have felt Corlys Velaryon's
envious gaze staring at me

480
00:39:41.127 --> 00:39:42.670
from across the Blackwater.

481
00:39:43.323 --> 00:39:46.424
You sit upon the highest seat
in the realm. Your Grace.

482
00:39:46.796 --> 00:39:49.131
Proud men don't like having to look up.

483
00:39:52.846 --> 00:39:54.807
Laena Velaryon.

484
00:39:56.100 --> 00:39:58.807
Lord Corlys is your Master of Ships

485
00:39:59.342 --> 00:40:03.137
and she is the eldest daughter
of the wealthiest house in the realm.

486
00:40:03.222 --> 00:40:06.791
She comes from
unimpeachable Valyrian stock

487
00:40:06.878 --> 00:40:09.385
and she has Targaryen blood.

488
00:40:09.470 --> 00:40:12.080
- What's to mislike?
- She is 12.

489
00:40:12.254 --> 00:40:13.797
She will mature.

490
00:40:16.255 --> 00:40:17.840
I never asked to remarry.

491
00:40:18.424 --> 00:40:21.552
As King. you have a claim on all things.

492
00:40:22.332 --> 00:40:23.791
Even those you don't want.

493
00:40:23.876 --> 00:40:26.534
Marriage is not an obligation
you can put off for long.

494
00:40:26.619 --> 00:40:29.246
What if I was to reject
Lord Corlys's proposal?

495
00:40:29.376 --> 00:40:31.629
He would not be like to take it well.

496
00:40:32.150 --> 00:40:35.946
I fear nothing short of a direct line
to the Iron Throne would satisfy him.

497
00:40:36.374 --> 00:40:39.159
You should also consider
that we find ourselves

498
00:40:39.244 --> 00:40:41.682
on the precipice of war in the Step stones.

499
00:40:42.077 --> 00:40:44.996
And the Sea Snake holds claim to nearly
half the realm's ships.

500
00:40:45.135 --> 00:40:48.271
He would not dare withhold them
in the face of the realm's need.

501
00:40:49.324 --> 00:40:52.919
- Who is he to hector me?
- No one. Your Grace.

502
00:40:54.113 --> 00:40:58.117
But Driftmark makes for a better ally
than it does an enemy.

503
00:40:59.180 --> 00:41:01.696
The Sea Snake has made a calculated reach.

504
00:41:01.781 --> 00:41:04.009
a fair play for a man of his position.

505
00:41:05.834 --> 00:41:08.318
If you truly want my unencumbered opinion.

506
00:41:08.403 --> 00:41:09.404
I do.

507
00:41:10.510 --> 00:41:13.022
You should wed Laena Velaryon. Your Grace.

508
00:41:13.709 --> 00:41:17.053
Sate Lord Corlys and fix him at your side.

509
00:41:17.138 --> 00:41:18.973
permanently. as an ally.

510
00:41:23.319 --> 00:41:24.695
Your Grace.

511
00:41:24.779 --> 00:41:27.781
the Princess has returned
from Dragons tone.

512
00:41:27.865 --> 00:41:29.533
Dragons tone?

513
00:41:48.426 --> 00:41:49.552
Your Grace.

514
00:41:53.463 --> 00:41:55.522
You disobeyed me.

515
00:41:55.607 --> 00:41:58.811
You fled King's Landing without a word

516
00:41:59.552 --> 00:42:02.967
and you acted without The Crown's leave.

517
00:42:05.970 --> 00:42:08.138
You are my only heir.

518
00:42:09.180 --> 00:42:11.098
You could've been killed.

519
00:42:14.648 --> 00:42:16.024
May I sit?

520
00:42:26.978 --> 00:42:29.006
You went to Dragons tone.

521
00:42:29.247 --> 00:42:31.319
And retrieved the egg without bloodshed.

522
00:42:33.400 --> 00:42:36.528
A feat I'm not sure Ser Otto
could've accomplished alone.

523
00:42:39.594 --> 00:42:41.471
Yes. well.

524
00:42:45.871 --> 00:42:48.629
I sometimes forget
how alike you both were.

525
00:42:58.121 --> 00:43:02.292
Your mother's absence
is a wound that will never heal.

526
00:43:03.530 --> 00:43:04.864
Without her.

527
00:43:05.655 --> 00:43:10.018
the Red Keep has lost a warmth
that I dare say it will never recover.

528
00:43:10.103 --> 00:43:13.231
It pleases me to hear you say this.

529
00:43:16.826 --> 00:43:20.120
To know that I'm not alone in my grief.

530
00:43:20.205 --> 00:43:22.623
I wish I had known better

531
00:43:22.708 --> 00:43:24.919
what to say to you in the aftermath.

532
00:43:27.237 --> 00:43:31.157
I struggled to realize that my daughter
had so quickly become a woman grown.

533
00:43:34.635 --> 00:43:36.178
But I know

534
00:43:37.020 --> 00:43:40.648
she understands
what is now expected of me.

535
00:43:40.733 --> 00:43:43.152
The King must take a new wife.

536
00:43:47.767 --> 00:43:49.894
I could never replace your mother.

537
00:43:51.877 --> 00:43:54.129
No more than I intend
to replace you as heir.

538
00:43:56.043 --> 00:43:58.211
But you are my only heir

539
00:43:58.296 --> 00:44:01.635
and our line is vulnerable.
too easily ended.

540
00:44:02.028 --> 00:44:04.486
And by marrying again.
I may begin to ensure

541
00:44:04.571 --> 00:44:05.814
that we are better defended.

542
00:44:05.899 --> 00:44:06.983
Against whom?

543
00:44:07.138 --> 00:44:09.278
Whomever may dare to challenge us.

544
00:44:15.513 --> 00:44:17.955
I do not wish to make us estranged.

545
00:44:18.756 --> 00:44:20.174
You are the King.

546
00:44:20.602 --> 00:44:23.963
and so. your first duty is to the realm.

547
00:44:27.150 --> 00:44:29.069
Mother would've understood this.

548
00:44:31.482 --> 00:44:33.025
Just as I do.

549
00:45:17.998 --> 00:45:20.037
Good morrow. my lords.

550
00:45:30.787 --> 00:45:34.332
I have decided to take a new wife.

551
00:45:51.704 --> 00:45:53.372
I intend to marry

552
00:45:59.843 --> 00:46:01.928
the Lady Alicent High tower

553
00:46:03.657 --> 00:46:05.576
before spring's end.

554
00:46:12.061 --> 00:46:13.873
This is an absurdity.

555
00:46:14.775 --> 00:46:17.428
My house is Valyrian.

556
00:46:17.513 --> 00:46:19.640
the greatest power in the realm.

557
00:46:20.789 --> 00:46:22.708
And I am your King.

558
00:46:46.428 --> 00:46:47.971
Rhaenyra.

559
00:47:09.119 --> 00:47:12.664
House Velaryon's origins
reach back to Old Valyria.

560
00:47:14.499 --> 00:47:17.044
More ancient even than House Targaryen

561
00:47:18.769 --> 00:47:20.687
according to some texts.

562
00:47:22.275 --> 00:47:24.438
But unlike the Targaryens.

563
00:47:24.882 --> 00:47:26.801
we were no dragon lords.

564
00:47:28.056 --> 00:47:32.351
For centuries. my house had to scratch out
an existence from the sea

565
00:47:32.435 --> 00:47:34.727
with grit and luck.

566
00:47:37.014 --> 00:47:39.274
When I ascended the Driftwood Throne.

567
00:47:40.437 --> 00:47:41.980
I knew what I wanted.

568
00:47:43.801 --> 00:47:45.719
So I went out and seized it.

569
00:47:47.239 --> 00:47:48.847
Unlike every other lord of the realm.

570
00:47:48.932 --> 00:47:51.766
I can say that I built
my house's high seat

571
00:47:51.851 --> 00:47:53.979
with the strength of mine own back.

572
00:48:00.101 --> 00:48:02.602
I've always thought of
you and I as having been

573
00:48:02.744 --> 00:48:04.496
made from the same cloth.

574
00:48:13.161 --> 00:48:15.696
I wasn't aware you had
a king for a brother.

575
00:48:15.836 --> 00:48:19.256
We're both men who have had to cut
our own way through the world.

576
00:48:20.179 --> 00:48:23.098
We've been passed over too often.

577
00:48:25.726 --> 00:48:27.164
Did you call me to Driftmark

578
00:48:27.249 --> 00:48:29.313
to remind me of my
low standing. Lord Corlys.

579
00:48:29.398 --> 00:48:31.316
or was there some other reason?

580
00:48:34.814 --> 00:48:36.899
You've heard of the troubles
in the Step stones?

581
00:48:39.738 --> 00:48:43.783
<i>Some Myrish Prince
is feeding Westerosi sailors to the crabs.</i>

582
00:48:43.868 --> 00:48:46.672
<i>I have been petitioning
the King to send my navy</i>

583
00:48:46.769 --> 00:48:48.479
<i>into the territory.</i>

584
00:48:48.564 --> 00:48:50.227
but he's denied me.

585
00:48:50.312 --> 00:48:52.305
It was never my brother's strongest trait.

586
00:48:52.504 --> 00:48:53.532
What?

587
00:48:54.757 --> 00:48:56.175
Being King.

588
00:49:00.664 --> 00:49:03.041
<i>The Crabfeeder is backed
by powerful entities</i>

589
00:49:03.126 --> 00:49:06.671
<i>within the Free Cities who wish to see
Westeros weakened.</i>

590
00:49:08.315 --> 00:49:11.902
<i>And the King's failures
have allowed him to accumulate strength.</i>

591
00:49:13.662 --> 00:49:16.381
If those shipping lanes fall.

592
00:49:16.503 --> 00:49:18.421
my house will be crippled.

593
00:49:19.215 --> 00:49:21.709
And I will not have Driftmark
beggared while our King

594
00:49:21.794 --> 00:49:24.998
idles himself with feasts.
and balls. and tourneys.

595
00:49:25.116 --> 00:49:28.036
I will speak of my brother as I wish.

596
00:49:29.534 --> 00:49:31.035
You will not.

597
00:49:34.597 --> 00:49:36.390
Waiting in the Step stones

598
00:49:36.475 --> 00:49:38.602
is a chance for you to prove your worth

599
00:49:38.687 --> 00:49:40.981
to any who might yet doubt it.

600
00:49:42.164 --> 00:49:44.708
We are the realm's second sons. Daemon.

601
00:49:46.072 --> 00:49:47.991
Our worth is not given.

602
00:49:49.546 --> 00:49:51.465
It must be made.

603
00:49:52.305 --> 00:50:52.903
